<div class="subheader-bar">
  <div class="sh-left"></div>
  <div class="sh-mid"><b>How to Play</b></div>
  <div class="sh-right"></div>
</div>

<table class="blizz-table" style="width:100%;">
  <tr><th colspan="2">Getting Started</th></tr>
  <tr>
    <td style="width:30px; text-align:center; color:#d0a803; font-weight:bold;">1</td>
    <td><b style="color:#d0a803;">Download the Client</b><br>Download World of Warcraft 3.3.5a (Wrath of the Lich King) client. You can find it via a quick web search for "WoW 3.3.5a client download".</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td style="text-align:center; color:#d0a803; font-weight:bold;">2</td>
    <td><b style="color:#d0a803;">Create an Account</b><br>Register an account on our website by clicking <a href="/auth/register" style="color:#d0a803;">Register</a>. Remember your username and password.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td style="text-align:center; color:#d0a803; font-weight:bold;">3</td>
    <td><b style="color:#d0a803;">Set the Realmlist</b><br>Navigate to your WoW installation folder and find <code style="color:#6f6;">Data/enUS/realmlist.wtf</code> (or your locale folder). Open it with a text editor and change it to:<br><br>
      <div style="background:#000; padding:6px 10px; border:1px solid #333; font-family:monospace; color:#6f6;">set realmlist <%= typeof siteConfig !== 'undefined' && siteConfig.realmlist ? siteConfig.realmlist : '127.0.0.1' %></div>
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td style="text-align:center; color:#d0a803; font-weight:bold;">4</td>
    <td><b style="color:#d0a803;">Launch &amp; Login</b><br>Run <code style="color:#6f6;">Wow.exe</code> (not the Launcher) and log in with the account you created on our website. Select your realm and create a character!</td>
  </tr>
</table>

<p style="margin-top:10px;">Need help? Check our <a href="/support/faq" style="color:#d0a803;">FAQ</a> or contact an administrator in-game.</p>
